cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with using images to classify apps, which involves computer vision techniques such as OCR, pic2vec, and object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as generating descriptions from images, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of machine learning algorithms such as SVM for classification falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and the use of image-based techniques for classification falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
